[00:00.61]	[A cavern. In the middle, a boiling cauldron.,]
[00:01.83]	[Thunder. Enter the three Witches]
[00:03.05]First Witch	Thrice the brinded cat hath mew'd.
[00:07.13]Second Witch	Thrice and once the hedge-pig whined.
[00:11.51]Third Witch	Harpier cries 'Tis time, 'tis time.
[00:15.38]First Witch	Round about the cauldron go;
[00:18.84]	In the poison'd entrails throw.
[00:22.61]	Toad, that under cold stone
[00:25.97]	Days and nights has thirty-one
[00:29.74]	Swelter'd venom sleeping got,
[00:33.31]	Boil thou first i' the charmed pot.
[00:37.38]ALL	Double, double toil and trouble;
[00:41.15]	Fire burn, and cauldron bubble.
[00:44.82]Second Witch	Fillet of a fenny snake,
[00:47.88]	In the cauldron boil and bake;
[00:51.55]	Eye of newt and toe of frog,
[00:55.01]	Wool of bat and tongue of dog,
[00:58.68]	Adder's fork and blind-worm's sting,
[01:02.96]	Lizard's leg and owlet's wing,
[01:06.62]	For a charm of powerful trouble,
[01:10.50]	Like a hell-broth boil and bubble.
[01:14.57]ALL	Double, double toil and trouble;
[01:18.34]	Fire burn and cauldron bubble.
[01:22.01]Third Witch	Scale of dragon, tooth of wolf,
[01:25.68]	Witches' mummy, maw and gulf
[01:29.04]	Of the ravin'd salt-sea shark,
[01:32.71]	Root of hemlock digg'd i' the dark,
[01:36.78]	Liver of blaspheming Jew,
[01:39.94]	Gall of goat, and slips of yew
[01:43.61]	Silver'd in the moon's eclipse,
[01:47.38]	Nose of Turk and Tartar's lips,
[01:51.15]	Finger of birth-strangled babe
[01:54.92]	Ditch-deliver'd by a drab,
[01:58.18]	Make the gruel thick and slab:
[02:01.84]	Add thereto a tiger's chaudron,
[02:05.61]	For the ingredients of our cauldron.
[02:09.89]ALL	Double, double toil and trouble;
[02:13.66]	Fire burn and cauldron bubble.
[02:17.33]Second Witch	Cool it with a baboon's blood,
[02:21.00]	Then the charm is firm and good.
[02:24.87]	[Enter HECATE to the other three Witches]
[02:26.09]HECATE	O well done! I commend your pains;
[02:30.06]	And every one shall share i' the gains;
[02:34.55]	And now about the cauldron sing,
[02:38.42]	Live elves and fairies in a ring,
[02:42.39]	Enchanting all that you put in.
[02:46.16]	[Music and a song: 'Black spirits,' &c]
[02:47.38]	[HECATE retires]
[02:48.61]Second Witch	By the pricking of my thumbs,
[02:52.17]	Something wicked this way comes.
[02:56.04]	Open, locks,
[02:57.78]	Whoever knocks!
[02:59.91]	[Enter MACBETH]
[03:01.14]MACBETH	How now, you secret, black, and midnight hags!
[03:06.13]	What is't you do?
[03:08.47]ALL	A deed without a name.
[03:11.33]MACBETH	I conjure you, by that which you profess,
[03:16.01]	Howe'er you come to know it, answer me:
[03:20.49]	Though you untie the winds and let them fight
[03:25.79]	Against the churches; though the yesty waves
[03:30.89]	Confound and swallow navigation up;
[03:35.06]	Though bladed corn be lodged and trees blown down;
[03:40.77]	Though castles topple on their warders' heads;
[03:45.96]	Though palaces and pyramids do slope
[03:50.35]	Their heads to their foundations; though the treasure
