[04:01.04]	Even till destruction sicken; answer me
[04:05.63]	To what I ask you.
[04:08.07]First Witch	Speak.
[04:09.29]Second Witch	Demand.
[04:10.62]Third Witch	We'll answer.
[04:12.55]First Witch	Say, if thou'dst rather hear it from our mouths,
[04:17.95]	Or from our masters?
[04:20.60]MACBETH	Call 'em; let me see 'em.
[04:23.46]First Witch	Pour in sow's blood, that hath eaten
[04:27.73]	Her nine farrow; grease that's sweaten
[04:32.22]	From the murderer's gibbet throw
[04:36.19]	Into the flame.
[04:38.33]ALL	Come, high or low;
[04:40.67]	Thyself and office deftly show!
[04:44.44]	[Thunder. First Apparition: an armed Head]
[04:45.67]MACBETH	Tell me, thou unknown power,--
[04:49.03]First Witch	He knows thy thought:
[04:51.78]	Hear his speech, but say thou nought.
[04:56.06]First Apparition	Macbeth! Macbeth! Macbeth! beware Macduff;
[05:00.64]	Beware the thane of Fife. Dismiss me. Enough.
