[06:12.06]	+ with a tree in his hand]
[06:12.67]	What is this
[06:14.61]	That rises like the issue of a king,
[06:18.89]	And wears upon his baby-brow the round
[06:23.47]	And top of sovereignty?
[06:26.42]ALL	Listen, but speak not to't.
[06:29.69]Third Apparition	Be lion-mettled, proud; and take no care
[06:34.27]	Who chafes, who frets, or where conspirers are:
[06:39.47]	Macbeth shall never vanquish'd be until
[06:44.15]	Great Birnam wood to high Dunsinane hill
[06:48.94]	Shall come against him.
[06:51.89]	[Descends]
[06:53.12]MACBETH	That will never be
[06:55.66]	Who can impress the forest, bid the tree
[07:00.35]	Unfix his earth-bound root? Sweet bodements! good!
[07:05.85]	Rebellion's head, rise never till the wood
